EXTRACTED VALUE: Much like the original Bully, Scholarship Edition is entertaining enough at times, but it never rises above being merely good.
Frequent fliers of the Ace Combat series will feel like they've been on this flight before. [Dec 2007, p.122]
It's Matt Leinart pretty, but lacks the gameplay polish found on the PlayStation 2 and Xbox.
The biggest knock against this game is it'll cost you $59.99 and it only offers up seven to nine hours of play.
Still an incredibly addictive game but there are a lot of racing games out there for the launch and this is just a port.
